Class CircularLinkedList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • kelmore5.java.yeh.data_structures.linked_lists.ListAdapter<T>
      • kelmore5.java.yeh.data_structures.linked_lists.CircularLinkedList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type parameter
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>

    public class CircularLinkedList<T>
extends ListAdapter<T>
     A Circular Linked List is a linked list that loops around to the
 front of the list. So, if you're traveling through the list, going past
 the end will bring you back to the root.
    Date:
    Fall 2012
